<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
This is an idea I had awhile ago, and I freely admit it could have some holes in it, but the blueprint in my mind is sound.<P>What to do when you reach a level that it is too hard to just solo, and is an event to do anything?  Some people twink, others powerlevel, and so on.  My idea is as follows:<P>BE A MOB.  Players that achieve a certain lofty status would be able to create a MOB in a brand new PC MOB zone.  In this zone, there would be regular NPC Mobs, but there would be many MOB camps, and wandering MOB zones, that all the mobs are real players.  I am not talking about PVP zones.  This would be an intelligent MOB zone.  <P>A zone where mobs cannot walk and see through walls.  The zone would be KARANAS in size with 20 "camp" spots.  Your MOB choices are as follows:<BR>1) A wandering MOB.  A lower level mob that can travel the entire zone.<BR>2) The Grouped MOB.  You and and up to 6 other Mobs spawn at a random camp.  Your equipment is randomly generated, but you can loot unlooted other mobs, to beef up.  Your range is limited by the distance of your camp, thus making it impossible to create a two or three camp army.<BR>3) The SMOB (smart mob) You and another Mob, spawn at your home base.  You can double up with one other mob, and wander the zones, attempting to ambush players.  The SMOB's are higher level than the Wandering Mobs.  With this scenario, one mob could wander aimlessly, hoping to be attacked, but your partner jumps out when Player jumps you.<BR>4)  The GMOB:  The Guard Mob.  You and your other player Mobs try to hold down your castle (town) which can be invaded by RAID type groups.  <P>As this NEW type Mob, you speak a special language that player characters cannot understand.  As soon as you are attacked, your own ATTACK goes on and stays on.  This prevents you from purposely dying to give a friend your loot. You cannot read a player name.  All you see is "A Human Warrior"  "A Dark Elf Necromancer" Furthermore, you can't sent tells to players letting the know you are going to lay down for them.  <BR>Simply put, you cannot communicate with a player.<P>When you die, you get respawned at some other random point.  <P>Okay, you cannot level up per se, you cannot loot a player, so what is in it for you?  <P>To see the world from another point of view.  If you can successfully kill X amount of players, you get to increase your ability. To give other players a challenge heretofore unseen.  Imagine the play of jumping a Player, and letting them hit you for whatever damage, and then you running from them...but running to an Ambush point, where your other 5 MOBS are lying in wait...<BR>(if you run right away, the player will know they are being suckered)<P>You could be a water-breathing mob, lying in wait under the water's surface for that cleric to sit down and med.  BAM, you thrust out of the water onto them!<P>There are many other possibilites, but if you had a chance to be a mob, would you do it?<P>--------------------<P>Host of the Newbie(r)Zone<BR>http://www.delphi.com/newbiezone/start <BR>    <BR>      Shokar Ke'Ravensali<BR>	Level 25 Paladin<BR>	Morrell-Thulle<BR>      Catyra Ke'Ravensmar<BR>	Level 22 Shaman<BR>	Morrell-Thulle
</FONT>
