This whole idea originally stemmed from a process of ideas.  There seems to be very little for the Uber Player to do except very involved raids and the like.  I got to thinking that UBER was such a great accomplishment, and that turning level 55 from 54 would be a little of a downer. <P>I may never get there, but what would I like?  Well in D&D, we got filthy rich and owned a city.  If I was level 50ish, I would love to go into a town and see a shop named after me.  Hail the keeper, and they tell a tale that YOU wrote about yourself, with a quest thrown in...<P>Hail to ye gentle traveler and welcome to Johhny Rotten's Pub.  [Johnny the Warrior] is not here right now, but ye will find our drinks to be the best in the land.<P>/say Who is Johnny?<P>Tis a [wonderful tale] and tis a [sad tale] of Johnny the Warrior, buy my a drink and I may tell ye of it...<P>And so on, with wonderful tale telling of you achievements, and sad telling of some long lost love, family, item, quest.<P>/say tell me a sad tale.<P>Poor Johnny lost his price wolf in [The Bawmy Bog] and was ne'r able to find him again.  Maybe an adventurer such as yourself would be willing to search the Bog for him?<P>Then from there, you get to go to the SMOB zone.  The city that leads to it has buildings, statues, stores etc, all named after PC's.  Get a screen shot of you standing next to a statue erected in your honor.  There could be an ingame hall of heros too.<P>But, as a bonus, when you get to HEROTOWN, you get to be a MOB.  Maybe this zone would have like 50 different types of mobs, and when you respawn, you never know what you are going to be.  There would have to be some sort of code in place preventing 85 mobs on one PC and such.<P>Dead unlooted SMOBS could be dragged at will by SMOBS, to serve as "bait" for unwitting travelers.  Every time you survive a batlle, you get SPOINTS (Smart Points)  This does not mean that you have to Kill something to get SP's, just live to fight another day.  Then you get the option of respawning as a better SMOB.  Your SPOINTS are cumulative to YOU, not the SMOB, so everytime you log on, you are not always an ORC pawn or some crap.  The Grand goal of course would be to be allowed into SMOB CITY Prime, the city that gets invaded by Raid groups.  <BR>Imagine being chased by players through your own city, but you are a SMOB, so you know where all the pit traps and ambush points are.  <P>/say is this smob RUNNING or LURING us?<P>Maybe add a Kith element to it, with NEW undead under the city, that the pit traps lead to.<P>The more Spoints you get, the more goodies you will spawn with.<P>SMOB SAFETY ZONES.  The Area would be divided into zones (not Loading Please Wait Zones) but areas where, well, let's say you see a player being attacked, and you want to join in.<P>(Sorry, that player is currently engaged in battle, and you cannot attack him)  <P>You would either lie in wait for the battle to end, or maybe talk to the SMOB and get him to fake injury and lure the Player to a zone where multiple SMOB attacks are permitted.<P>CAMPS by players would be accepted by a command, and recognized by a /who camp command for players.  Since the SMOB zone would have 50 camps, there is plenty to go around.  What this means is that two player groups could not jump the SMOB camp, nor could two SMOB camps jump the players.  The only Smobs allowed to attack the players in this situation would be the Wandering Smobs.<P>Live or die, you get SPOINTS for the battle, determined on the player level, and the damage you did to it.  As an example, a Blue player that you do 100 damage to would net you 100 SPOINTS, a green player that you do 100 points of damage to would net you maybe 1/4 of that...(25 Spoints) and a yellow player would net you 150 spoints for the damage you do.  Of course, all kills would be triple Spoints.<P>Do I think too much?<P>--------------------<P>Host of the Newbie(r)Zone<BR>http://www.delphi.com/newbiezone/start <BR>    <BR>      Shokar Ke'Ravensali<BR>	Level 25 Paladin<BR>	Morrell-Thulle<BR>      Catyra Ke'Ravensmar<BR>	Level 22 Shaman<BR>	Morrell-Thulle
</FONT>
