Yes, it is an excellent idea, however, there is no way in my wildest dreams could I imagine something like this going through with EQ. PvP is broken, and VI is adding more of the same. Maybe Shadows of Luclin will make some changes/improvements, but we'll have to wait and see.<P>In the meantime, check out <A HREF="http://www.darkageofcamelot.com/index.html" TARGET=_blank>http://www.darkageofcamelot.com/index.html</A> <P>Their ideas are remarkably similar in many aspects to yours. There are three different realms, far away from each other, that are hostile. Each realm is composed of players, who are completely unable to communicate with each other. From what the developers are putting forth, it seems that it'll be possible to do pure PvM, or to advance to PvP (Which will net realm points). Attacking another realm would be like a plane raid...against PCs. Valuable resources would be on the frontiers, encouraging conflicts. Dark Age of Camelot, if it works, sounds great. When you raid an enemy city or fort, the defenders are real people, with real strategy.
